n Old Celtic name meaning ‘born of Esos’. Esos (or Aesos) was a Celtic god known to have been the subject of a cult in ancient Gaul."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Owain ap Bleddyn was born in 1210, in Corwen, Merionethshire, Wales, his father, Bleddyn ap Owain Brogyntyn, was 40 and his mother, Margaret FERCH GWYN, was 43. He married Gwenllian verch Madog ap Rhirld Flaidd of Pennant Melangell about 1250, in Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons. He died in 1267, in Powys, Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 57."},"et":{"1210–1267":"1210–1267","1205–Female":"1205–Surnud","1240–1320":"1240–1320","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1245–Male":"1245–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1262–Male":"1262–Surnud","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1168–Female":"1168–Surnud","about 1250":"umbes 1250","1262":"1262","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1170":"1170","1205":"1205","Abt 1250":"umbes 1250","1245":"1245","1267":"1267","1168":"1168","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","about 1245":"umbes 1245","about 1262":"umbes 1262","Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Dinmael, Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","Corwen, Merionethshire, Wales":"Corwen, Merionethshire, Wales","Powys, Wales":"Powys, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1210–1267":"1210–1267","1205–Female":"1205–Kuollut","1240–1320":"1240–1320","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1245–Male":"1245–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1262–Male":"1262–Kuollut","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1168–Female":"1168–Kuollut","about 1250":"noin 1250","1262":"1262","1240":"1240","1250":"1250","1170":"1170","1205":"1205","Abt 1250":"noin 1250","1245":"1245","1267":"1267","1168":"1168","1210":"1210","1320":"1320","about 1245":"noin 1245","about 1262":"noin 1262","Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dinmael, Denbighshire, Wales":"Denbighshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunt